  "texts": [
    "This allows us to measure the success probability of the gate operation, which is defined as the ratio of coincidence counts in the target output modes over the total coincidence counts integrated over all outputs in one polarization channel.",
    "We perform this measurement on three randomly chosen implementations of the gate 𝔽𝔽 in two, three and five dimensions and measure a success probability of 0.36 ± 0.01, 0.27 ± 0.03 and 0.18 ± 0.04, respectively (Methods provides additional details).",
    "It is worth noting that for this proof-of-concept demonstration, we only control a single polarization channel of the MMF, thus reducing the success probability by about half.",
    "Controlling both polarization channels of the MMF can increase the success probability by almost a factor of two as well as improve the fidelity of the implemented circuits.",
    "Errors in the fidelities are calculated by taking into account the photon-counting statistics as well as systematic errors due to misalignments."
  ],
